The 74LS461 chips are PALs and due to a 5 MHz bus CPU09CMI 
they become very hot at an ambient temperature above 35 degrees Celsius.

The 74LS461 temperature rises to 60 degrees Celsius in no time, 
and without a fan the system is in trouble.

Replace the 74LS461 chips with a GAL22V10-15 programmed with GALUX-461.jed, 
see UniFLEX section.

The system now runs without any problems 
and the chips remain at around 40 degrees Celsius.


